==English==

===Etymology===
Recorded since 1656; from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|lang=grc|εὐφημισμός|tr=euphēmismos}}, from {{term|lang=grc|εὐφημίζω|tr=euphēmizō}}, from {{term|lang=grc|εὔφημος|tr=euphēmos||uttering sound of good omen, abstaining from inauspicious words}}, from {{term|εὖ||well|tr=eu|lang=grc}} + {{term|lang=grc|φήμη|tr=phēmē||a voice, a prophetic voice, rumor, talk}}, from {{term|lang=grc|φάναι|tr=phanai||to speak, say}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|yoo͞'fə-mĭz"(ə)m}}, {{IPA|/ˈjuː.fəˌmɪ.z(ə)m/}}

===Noun===
{{examples-right|examples=
* ''[[fib]]'' for ''[[lie#noun_2|lie]]''
* ''correctional facility'' for ''[[prison]]'' (compare [[dysphemism]]: ''[[slammer]]'')
* ''[[sleep with|sleep (with)]]'' for ''[[have sex|have sex (with)]]'' (compare [[dysphemism]]s: ''[[bang]]'', ''[[fuck]]'')
* ''[[pass away]]'' for ''[[die#verb|die]]''
* ''vertically challenged'' for ''[[short]]'' (physical stature; compare [[dysphemism]]s: ''[[midget]]'', ''[[dwarf]]'')
}}
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The use of a word or phrase to replace another with one that is considered less [[offensive]], [[blunt]] or [[vulgar]] than the word or phrase it replaces.
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} A word or phrase that is used to replace another in this way.

